$PROBLEM PK MODEL ORAL ADMINISTRATION

  ; NUMBER OF COMPARTMENTS        : 1 OR 2 OR 3
  ;
  ; ABSORPTION                    : FIRST-ORDER (option of LAG TIME), ZERO-ORDER OR ZERO-ORDER FOLLOWED BY FIRST-ORDER
  ;
  ; ELIMINATION                   : FIRST-ORDER
  ;
  ; INTERINDIVIDUAL VARIABILITY   : ESTIMATE in all parameters or fixed in some of them to 15% CV.
  ;
  ; RESIDUAL ERROR FOR PLASMA OBS : PROPORTIONAL, ADDITIVE OR COMBINED


$INPUT C ID TIME TAD AMT EVID DV II ADDL DOSE DOSEREF DAY RATE

$DATA /projects/qcp/QCP_MODELING/OTHER/autoPK/automatization_popPK/DerivedData/toymodel_data_rate_dose.csv
  IGNORE=@

$SUBROUTINE ADVAN5

$MODEL
  NCOMP= 3 
  COMP = (DEPOT, INITIALOFF) 
  COMP = (CENTRAL ) 
  COMP = (PERIPH) 




$PK
  ; Parameter definition

  TVCL=EXP(THETA(1))    ; CL
  TVV2= EXP(THETA(2))   ; V2
  TVKA=EXP(THETA(4))    ; KA
  TVV3=EXP(THETA(7)) ; V3 
  TVQ=EXP(THETA(8)) ; Q 




  ; MU Referencing
  MU_1  = LOG(TVCL) + 0    ; CL
  MU_2  = LOG(TVV2) + LOG(DOSE/DOSEREF)*THETA(3)    ; V2
  MU_3  = LOG(TVKA) + 0    ; KA
  MU_4  = LOG(TVV3) + 0  ; V3 
  MU_5  = LOG(TVQ) + LOG(DOSE/DOSEREF)*THETA(9) ; Q 



  ; Parameter transformations
  CL   = EXP(MU_1 + ETA(1))  ; CL
  V2    = EXP(MU_2 + ETA(2)) ; V2
  KA   = EXP(MU_3 + ETA(3))  ; KA
  V3   = EXP(MU_4 + ETA(4)) ; V3  
  Q   = EXP(MU_5 + ETA(5)) ; Q


  TVD1=EXP(THETA(10)) 
  MU_6  = LOG(TVD1) ; D1 
  D1 = EXP(MU_6 + ETA(6))  ; D1


  ; Assigning expressions to match ADVAN5 parameterization
  k12 = KA 
  k20 = CL/V2
  k20 = CL/V2
  k23 = Q/V2 ; k23  
  k32 = Q/V3 ; k32 


  F1 = 1   ; INPUT1
  S2 = V2 ; CP   

$ERROR
  CP = A(2)/S2
  IPRED = CP
  IRES = DV - IPRED
  W = SQRT(THETA(5)**2 + (THETA(6)*IPRED)**2)
  IWRES = IRES/W
  Y = IPRED + W*ERR(1)

$THETA
  ; Model parameters
  (2.5)       ; CL ; L/h ; LOG
  7         ; V2 ; L ; LOG

  0.1 	; cov_V2  ; 


  -1.5 	; KA ; h-1 ; LOG  

  ; Error model parameters
  0 FIX 	 ; add_error 
  (0, 0.2) 	 ; prop_error 

  ; Additional model parameters
  5 	 ; V3 ; LOG 
  2 	 ; Q ; LOG 
  0.1 	; cov_Q  ; 


  -1.2 	; D1  ; h ; LOG 




$OMEGA ;; search band
  0.1  ;  CL ; LOG
  0.1  ;  V2 ; LOG
  0.1 	;  KA ; LOG  

  0.1 	 ; V3 ; LOG 
  0.1 	 ; Q ; LOG

  0.0225 FIX 	 ; D1 ; LOG 



$SIGMA
  1 FIX


$ESTIMATION method = SAEM ISAMPLE = 2 NBURN = 1000 NITER = 500 RANMETHOD = 3S2P CTYPE = 3 CITER = 10 CALPHA = 0.05 CINTERVAL = 10 SEED = 234567 PRINT = 5 NOABORT INTERACTION
$ESTIMATION method = IMP ISAMPLE = 3000 EONLY = 1 NITER = 10 RANMETHOD = 3S2P NOABORT INTERACTION PRINT = 1 MAPITER = 0 SIGDIGITS = 3 NSIG = 3 SIGL = 9

$COVARIANCE UNCONDITIONAL MATRIX=R PRINT = E

$MODEL
  NCOMP= 6 
  COMP = (DEPOT, INITIALOFF)

  COMP = (TRANSIT1) 
  COMP = (TRANSIT2)

  0.1 	; cov_V2  ; 

  0.1 	; cov_KA  ; 

  -1.5 	; KA ; h-1 ; LOG  

  ; Error model parameters
  1.5 	 ; add_error 
  0 FIX 	 ; prop_error 

  ; Additional model parameters

  -1.2 	; ALAG1  ; h ; LOG 





$OMEGA ;; search band
  0.1  ;  CL ; LOG
  0.1  ;  V2 ; LOG
  0.1 	;  KA ; LOG  


  0.01 FIX 	 ; ALAG1 ; LOG 




$SIGMA
  1 FIX

$SUBROUTINE ADVAN5

$MODEL
  NCOMP= 4 
  COMP = (DEPOT, INITIALOFF) 
  COMP = (CENTRAL , DEFDOSE) 
  COMP = (PERIPH) 
  COMP = (PERIPH2) 




$PK
  ; Parameter definition

  TVCL=EXP(THETA(1))    ; CL
  TVV2= EXP(THETA(2))   ; V2
  TVKA=EXP(THETA(3))    ; KA
  TVV3=EXP(THETA(6)) 
  TVQ=EXP(THETA(7)) 
  TVV4=EXP(THETA(8)) 
  TVQ2=EXP(THETA(9)) 




  ; MU Referencing
  MU_1  = LOG(TVCL) + 0    ; CL
  MU_2  = LOG(TVV2) + 0    ; V2
  MU_3  = LOG(TVKA) + 0    ; KA
  MU_4  = LOG(TVV3) ; V3 
  MU_5  = LOG(TVQ) ; Q 
  MU_6  = LOG(TVV4) ; V4 
  MU_7  = LOG(TVQ2) ; Q2 



  ; Parameter transformations
  CL   = EXP(MU_1 + ETA(1))  ; CL
  V2    = EXP(MU_2 + ETA(2)) ; V2
  KA   = EXP(MU_3 + ETA(3))  ; KA
  V3 = EXP(MU_4 + ETA(4))  ; V3 
  Q = EXP(MU_5 + ETA(5)) ; Q 
  V4 = EXP(MU_6 + ETA(6))  ; V4 
  Q2   = EXP(MU_7 + ETA(7)) ; Q2

  TVALAG2=EXP(THETA(10)) 
  MU_8  = LOG(TVALAG2) ; ALAG2 
  ALAG2 = EXP(MU_8 + ETA(8))  ; ALAG2
  TVD2=EXP(THETA(11)) 
  MU_9  = LOG(TVD2) ; D2 
  D2 = EXP(MU_9 + ETA(9))  ; D2


  ; Assigning expressions to match ADVAN5 parameterization
  k20 = CL/V2
  k20 = CL/V2
  k23 = Q/V2  ; k23 
  k32 = Q/V3 ; k32 
  k24 = Q2/V2  ; k24 
  k42 = Q2/V4 ; k42 


  F1 = 1   ; INPUT1
  S2 = V2 ; CP   

$ERROR
  CP = A(2)/S2
  IPRED = CP
  IRES = DV - IPRED
  W = SQRT(THETA(4)**2 + (THETA(5)*IPRED)**2)
  IWRES = IRES/W
  Y = IPRED + W*ERR(1)

$THETA
  ; Model parameters
  (2.5)       ; CL ; L/h ; LOG
  7         ; V2 ; L ; LOG



  0 FIX 	; KA  ; 1/h ; LOG 

  ; Error model parameters
  0 FIX 	 ; add_error 
  (0, 0.2) 	 ; prop_error 

  ; Additional model parameters
  5 	 ; V3 ; LOG 
  2 	 ; Q ; LOG 
  4 	 ; V4 ; LOG 
  1.5 	 ; Q2 ; LOG 

  -1.2 	; ALAG2  ; h ; LOG 

  -1.2 	; D2  ; h ; LOG 




$OMEGA ;; search band
  0.1  ;  CL ; LOG
  0.1  ;  V2 ; LOG
  0 FIX ;  KA ; LOG  

  0.1 	 ; V3 ; LOG 
  0.0225 FIX 	 ; Q ; LOG 
  0.1 	 ; V4 ; LOG 
  0.0225 FIX 	 ; Q2 ; LOG
  0.01 FIX 	 ; ALAG2 ; LOG 

  0.1 	 ; D2 ; LOG 



$SIGMA
  1 FIX

  COMP = (DEPOT, INITIALOFF) 
  COMP = (CENTRAL , DEFDOSE) 
  COMP = (PERIPH) 
  COMP = (PERIPH2) 




$PK
  ; Parameter definition

  TVCL=EXP(THETA(1))    ; CL
  TVV2= EXP(THETA(2))   ; V2
  TVKA=EXP(THETA(5))    ; KA
  TVV3=EXP(THETA(8)) 
  TVQ=EXP(THETA(9)) 
  TVV4=EXP(THETA(10)) 
  TVQ2=EXP(THETA(11)) 




  ; MU Referencing
  MU_1  = LOG(TVCL) + LOG(DOSE/DOSEREF)*THETA(3)    ; CL
  MU_2  = LOG(TVV2) + 0    ; V2
  MU_3  = LOG(TVKA) + LOG(DOSE/DOSEREF)*THETA(4)    ; KA
  MU_4  = LOG(TVV3) ; V3 
  MU_5  = LOG(TVQ) ; Q 
  MU_6  = LOG(TVV4) ; V4 
  MU_7  = LOG(TVQ2) ; Q2 



  ; Parameter transformations
  CL   = EXP(MU_1 + ETA(1))  ; CL
  V2    = EXP(MU_2 + ETA(2)) ; V2
  KA   = EXP(MU_3 + ETA(3))  ; KA
  V3 = EXP(MU_4 + ETA(4))  ; V3 
  Q = EXP(MU_5 + ETA(5)) ; Q 
  V4 = EXP(MU_6 + ETA(6))  ; V4 
  Q2   = EXP(MU_7 + ETA(7)) ; Q2


  TVD2=EXP(THETA(12)) 
  MU_8  = LOG(TVD2) ; D2 
  D2 = EXP(MU_8 + ETA(8))  ; D2


  ; Assigning expressions to match ADVAN5 parameterization
  k20 = CL/V2
  k20 = CL/V2
  k23 = Q/V2  ; k23 
  k32 = Q/V3 ; k32 
  k24 = Q2/V2  ; k24 
  k42 = Q2/V4 ; k42 


  F1 = 1   ; INPUT1
  S2 = V2 ; CP   

$ERROR
  CP = A(2)/S2
  IPRED = CP
  IRES = DV - IPRED
  W = SQRT(THETA(6)**2 + (THETA(7)*IPRED)**2)
  IWRES = IRES/W
  Y = IPRED + W*ERR(1)

$THETA
  ; Model parameters
  (2.5)       ; CL ; L/h ; LOG
  7         ; V2 ; L ; LOG
  0.1 	; cov_CL  ; 


  0.1 	; cov_KA  ; 

  0 FIX 	; KA  ; 1/h ; LOG 

  ; Error model parameters
  1.5 	 ; add_error 
  (0, 0.2) 	 ; prop_error 

  ; Additional model parameters
  5 	 ; V3 ; LOG 
  2 	 ; Q ; LOG 
  4 	 ; V4 ; LOG 
  1.5 	 ; Q2 ; LOG 


  -1.2 	; D2  ; h ; LOG 




$OMEGA ;; search band
  0.1  ;  CL ; LOG
  0.1  ;  V2 ; LOG
  0 FIX ;  KA ; LOG  

  0.1 	 ; V3 ; LOG 
  0.1 	 ; Q ; LOG 
  0.0225 FIX 	 ; V4 ; LOG 
  0.1 	 ; Q2 ; LOG

  0.01 FIX 	 ; D2 ; LOG 



$SIGMA
  1 FIX

  COMP = (DEPOT, INITIALOFF) 
  COMP = (CENTRAL ) 
  COMP = (PERIPH) 
  COMP = (PERIPH2) 
  COMP = (TRANSIT1) 
  COMP = (TRANSIT2) 




$PK
  ; Parameter definition

  TVCL=EXP(THETA(1))    ; CL
  TVV2= EXP(THETA(2))   ; V2
  TVKA=EXP(THETA(4))    ; KA
  TVV3=EXP(THETA(7)) 
  TVQ=EXP(THETA(8)) 
  TVV4=EXP(THETA(9)) 
  TVQ2=EXP(THETA(10)) 




  ; MU Referencing
  MU_1  = LOG(TVCL) + LOG(DOSE/DOSEREF)*THETA(3)    ; CL
  MU_2  = LOG(TVV2) + 0    ; V2
  MU_3  = LOG(TVKA) + 0    ; KA
  MU_4  = LOG(TVV3) ; V3 
  MU_5  = LOG(TVQ) ; Q 
  MU_6  = LOG(TVV4) ; V4 
  MU_7  = LOG(TVQ2) ; Q2 



  ; Parameter transformations
  CL   = EXP(MU_1 + ETA(1))  ; CL
  V2    = EXP(MU_2 + ETA(2)) ; V2
  KA   = EXP(MU_3 + ETA(3))  ; KA
  V3 = EXP(MU_4 + ETA(4))  ; V3 
  Q = EXP(MU_5 + ETA(5)) ; Q 
  V4 = EXP(MU_6 + ETA(6))  ; V4 
  Q2   = EXP(MU_7 + ETA(7)) ; Q2





  ; Assigning expressions to match ADVAN5 parameterization
  k15 = KA 
  k56 = KA 
  k62 = KA
  k20 = CL/V2
  k23 = Q/V2  ; k23 
  k32 = Q/V3 ; k32 
  k24 = Q2/V2  ; k24 
  k42 = Q2/V4 ; k42 


  F1 = 1   ; INPUT1
  S2 = V2 ; CP   

$ERROR
  CP = A(2)/S2
  IPRED = CP
  IRES = DV - IPRED
  W = SQRT(THETA(5)**2 + (THETA(6)*IPRED)**2)
  IWRES = IRES/W
  Y = IPRED + W*ERR(1)

$THETA
  ; Model parameters
  (2.5)       ; CL ; L/h ; LOG
  7         ; V2 ; L ; LOG
  0.1 	; cov_CL  ; 



  -1.5 	; KA ; h-1 ; LOG  

  ; Error model parameters
  1.5 	 ; add_error 
  (0, 0.2) 	 ; prop_error 

  ; Additional model parameters
  5 	 ; V3 ; LOG 
  2 	 ; Q ; LOG 
  4 	 ; V4 ; LOG 
  1.5 	 ; Q2 ; LOG 






$OMEGA ;; search band
  0.1  ;  CL ; LOG
  0.1  ;  V2 ; LOG
  0.1 	;  KA ; LOG  

  0.1 	 ; V3 ; LOG 
  0.1 	 ; Q ; LOG 
  0.0225 FIX 	 ; V4 ; LOG 
  0.1 	 ; Q2 ; LOG




$SIGMA
  1 FIX


$ESTIMATION method = SAEM ISAMPLE = 2 NBURN = 1000 NITER = 500 RANMETHOD = 3S2P CTYPE = 3 CITER = 10 CALPHA = 0.05 CINTERVAL = 10 SEED = 234567 PRINT = 5 NOABORT INTERACTION
